author: jefft
msg: Changed Enum and ValuedEnum's constructors from public to protected access.
When they were public, the user of the Enum could add new Enum items at any
time, thereby breaking type safety. By making the constructors protected, only
the intended usage is supported, namely defining all Enum items inside a
subclass. This is illustrated in the javadocs.
